<font color="#FF0000">HOUSECLEANING</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 10 11:16:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
In case you haven't noticed, we're doing a housecleaning here.  I've posted the following message on the main dialogue page (the one which lists all the threads here):<br><br>
&quot;It is now one year since this site was launched.  <br><br>
&quot;This dialogue area was meant to encourage exchanges about how our lives and our society have been impacted by the Vietnam experience.<br><br>
&quot;While the discussions have sometimes been heated, people's ability to &quot;dialogue across differences&quot; has been inspiring.<br><br>
&quot;Now the posts seem to be deteriorating into personal insults. <br><br>
&quot;If folks can't get back on track, we will regrettably be forced to shut the dialogue down.&quot;<br><br>
I've closed down several of the un-named threads and will probably be closing this and several more down in the days to come.  I'm not going to let this site become the playground for a handful of people who have nothing better to do than insult each other.  Play nice, guys, or take it elsewhere.<br><br>
Feel free to post responses here, or privately to the address below.
<p><code>-- mnweiss@pov.org  (Marc Weiss) </code><p>


